</h3><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-bQtKYq czWvgn pf-34_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-35_ pf-text-1"><strong>Solicitor </strong>- A legal professional qualified to offer advice, represent clients in court, and conduct legal transactions.</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-37_ pf-text-1"><strong>Regulation</strong> - The act of controlling or governing according to standards or laws.</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-39_ pf-text-1"><strong>Compliance </strong>- Adherence to laws, regulations, guidelines, and specifications relevant to an organisation's operations.





